{"id":"2111.05554","submitter":"Vaibhav Prakash","authors":"Vaibhav N Prakash, Aranya Bhuti Bhattacherjee","title":"Decoherence control of a single-photon optomechanical system in\n  phase-sensitive reservoirs","comments":"18 pages, 4 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph physics.optics","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/","abstract":"  With technological advancements to achieve strong single-photon\noptomechanical coupling it becomes necessary to explore the effect of such a\nstrongly coupled system interacting with the environment. In this limit the\nstandard Lindblad master equation for the quantum optical case does not hold\nbecause it does not take into account the correct eigenstates. Hence another\ntype of master equation which is the Dressed-state master equation is used. In\norder to emphasize its use we report on the effect of squeezed vacuum/squeezed\nthermal reservoir on the decoherence of cavity photon Fock states in an\noptomechanical system in the strong single-photon coupling regime. We not only\ndemonstrate that this decoherence can be effectively controlled by changing the\nparameters of the reservoir but that such a control can occur via a cavity\ndephasing term at high enough reservoir temperatures. The presence of cavity\ndephasing term is an outcome of using correct eigenstates in the strong\nsingle-photon optomechanical coupling regime. This study is also different from\nprevious studies of system interacting with phase-sensitive reservoirs where\nsuch a dephasing term is absent. Our study might be important in understanding\ninformation processing in strongly coupled photonic systems and quantum\nmemories.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Nov 2021 07:31:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Dec 2021 13:18:07 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 30 Jun 2022 14:05:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-01"}
